        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2470854542" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2825151055692705302">“A man went to knock on the king&apos;s door and said, Give me a boat.” One of the best incipit ever! The Tale of the Unknown Island is about the desire to go after what we don’t know. The topic is developed through a very short yet deep allegorical tale crossing the dimensions of dream and reality to go after that of an imaginary unknown island. The theme of the island with its symbolic and archetypical implications is always particularly appealing to my imagination so I really enjoyed reading this </span>
  <span id="freeText2825151055692705302" style="display:none">“A man went to knock on the king's door and said, Give me a boat.” One of the best incipit ever! The Tale of the Unknown Island is about the desire to go after what we don’t know. The topic is developed through a very short yet deep allegorical tale crossing the dimensions of dream and reality to go after that of an imaginary unknown island. The theme of the island with its symbolic and archetypical implications is always particularly appealing to my imagination so I really enjoyed reading this tiny book. </span>
