<div id="review_1890061860" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1890061860" />
    <a title="Apoorv  Jagtap" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54703246-apoorv-jagtap"><img alt="Apoorv  Jagtap" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1460102352p2/54703246.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1890061860?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Apoorv  Jagtap" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Apoorv  Jagtap" href="/user/show/54703246-apoorv-jagtap">Apoorv  Jagtap</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1890061860&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1890061860" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16806942893117893966">A man waits by the king&apos;s door to make a request for a boat. The king ignores him and engages himself with favors (given to him). The man being stubborn refuses to leave and since only one man can request, the king is left with no choice but to confront the man. <br/><br/>After back and forth questioning regarding the purpose of a request for boat, the king finally agrees to fulfill his demand. The man reasons that he intends to find an unknown island although almost everyone in the city is convinced that</span>
  <span id="freeText16806942893117893966" style="display:none">A man waits by the king's door to make a request for a boat. The king ignores him and engages himself with favors (given to him). The man being stubborn refuses to leave and since only one man can request, the king is left with no choice but to confront the man. <br /><br />After back and forth questioning regarding the purpose of a request for boat, the king finally agrees to fulfill his demand. The man reasons that he intends to find an unknown island although almost everyone in the city is convinced that such a place does not exist and its only in the man's head. Nonetheless, he is accompanied with a woman who used to serve as a cleaner at the king's palace, now offering her service to the man. <br /><br />The man sets out to find a crew, but is disappointed at the end of the day. After returning, both of them inspect the boat, eat a meal and have a discussion before finally setting out to sleep. The man is clearly in love with the woman and vice versa but both are unable to express their feelings. Next day, much to their surprise a lot of crew men have joined, along with woman and several types of animals. Soon the man realizes that the true motive of the men was not to go in search for unknown island but find a better life on a different island. Upon reaching one, the man let's the entire crew set off for their journey. In the end, the man dreams about being around the woman as though both of them have been combined as one.<br /><br />The book is an interesting read, and would take less than an hour to complete. The reader in the end understands that the man was a dreamer. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16806942893117893966" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


