<div id="review_173997634" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/173997634" />
    <a title="Mark Picketts" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/644347-mark-picketts"><img alt="Mark Picketts" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1235421653p2/644347.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/173997634?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mark Picketts" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mark Picketts" href="/user/show/644347-mark-picketts">Mark Picketts</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer173997634" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7416137331669272411">I love <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1285555.Jos_Saramago' rel='nofollow noopener'>Saramago</a>, i did before reading this and am just trying to spread out reading all his works so I don&apos;t run out them.<br/><br/>Simple and beautiful, this will be the best use of your time - and it won&apos;t take much of that. <br/><br/><blockquote>
  <i>&quot;indeed this is the way fate usually treats us, it&apos;s there right behind us, it has already reached out a hand to touch us on the shoulder while we&apos;re still mutter to ourselves,&quot; - 38%<br/><br/>&quot;I know that even known islands remain unknown until we set foot on them,&quot; - 45%<br/><br/>&quot;Liking is probab</i></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText7416137331669272411" style="display:none">I love <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1285555.Jos_Saramago" rel="nofollow noopener">Saramago</a>, i did before reading this and am just trying to spread out reading all his works so I don't run out them.<br /><br />Simple and beautiful, this will be the best use of your time - and it won't take much of that. <br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>"indeed this is the way fate usually treats us, it's there right behind us, it has already reached out a hand to touch us on the shoulder while we're still mutter to ourselves," - 38%<br /><br />"I know that even known islands remain unknown until we set foot on them," - 45%<br /><br />"Liking is probably the best form of ownership, and ownership the worst form of liking." - 51%<br /><br />"don't you know, if you don't step outside yourself, you'll never discover who you are" - 65%<br /><br />"What do you think, That you have to leave the island in order to see the island, that we can't see ourselves unless we become free of ourselves, Unless we escape from ourselves, you mean, No, that's not the same thing" - 65%<br /><br />"sleep is a skilled magician, it changes the proportions of things, the distances between them, it separates people and they're lying next to each other, brings them together and they can barely see one another" - 81%</i>
</blockquote><br /><br />I can't wait to finish Huck Finn so Ollie can enjoy this one (or so i have an excuse to read it again).</span>
  <a data-text-id="7416137331669272411" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
