        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer101649128" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9528831041532813268">Once again Jose Saramago delivers an evocative story in his decptively simple style. The system for requesting favors from the king illustrated the truth behind every government&apos;s red tape. The power of the story, however, comes from the faith underlying the search for the unknown island. One of the main characters is a man who insists he will search for an island which has never been charted and is therefore unknown. The woman who cleans the castle decides the search sounds like the life she wa</span>
  <span id="freeText9528831041532813268" style="display:none">Once again Jose Saramago delivers an evocative story in his decptively simple style. The system for requesting favors from the king illustrated the truth behind every government's red tape. The power of the story, however, comes from the faith underlying the search for the unknown island. One of the main characters is a man who insists he will search for an island which has never been charted and is therefore unknown. The woman who cleans the castle decides the search sounds like the life she wants to lead. The two manage to find what the unknown island really means in terms of what every person needs. </span>
