        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3359416580" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8945368289118741959">It reminds me of Herman Melville&apos;s Bartebly, on a smaller scale, both main characters are men who are persistent in something that we, the readers, don&apos;t understand. Bartebly in his constant refusal, and the man who asks for a boat.<br/>A boat to do what? Visit an unknown island, an adventure that comes from a deep desire of something that he can&apos;t put into words, and almost no one understands. Until someone does.</span>
  <span id="freeText8945368289118741959" style="display:none">It reminds me of Herman Melville's Bartebly, on a smaller scale, both main characters are men who are persistent in something that we, the readers, don't understand. Bartebly in his constant refusal, and the man who asks for a boat.<br />A boat to do what? Visit an unknown island, an adventure that comes from a deep desire of something that he can't put into words, and almost no one understands. Until someone does.</span>
